    "csaf_version": "2.0",
    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for libcap.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 8.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "Libcap is a library for getting and setting POSIX.1e (formerly POSIX 6) draft 15 capabilities.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* libcap: Integer Overflow in _libcap_strdup() (CVE-2023-2603)\n\n* libcap: Memory Leak on pthread_create() Error (CVE-2023-2602)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
    ],
